Creates a new `PathBuf` with a given capacity used to create the internal [`OsString`](../ffi/struct.OsString.html "struct std::ffi::OsString"). See [`with_capacity`](about:blank/ffi/struct.OsString.html#method.with_capacity "associated function std::ffi::OsString::with_capacity") defined on [`OsString`](../ffi/struct.OsString.html "struct std::ffi::OsString").

##### [Â§](#examples-2)Examples

```
use std::path::PathBuf;

let mut path = PathBuf::with_capacity(10);
let capacity = path.capacity();

// This push is done without reallocating
path.push(r"C:\");

assert_eq!(capacity, path.capacity());
```

