let path = Path::new("foo.txt");
assert_eq!(path.to_string_lossy(), "foo.txt");
```

[Run](https://play.rust-lang.org/?code=%23!%5Ballow(unused)%5D%0Afn+main()+%7B%0A++++use+std::path::Path;%0A++++%0A++++let+path+=+Path::new(%22foo.txt%22);%0A++++assert_eq!(path.to_string_lossy(),+%22foo.txt%22);%0A%7D&edition=2021)

Had `path` contained invalid unicode, the `to_string_lossy` call might have returned `"foï¿½.txt"`.

